{
  "text": "To give an example of rules satisfying independence of irrelevant opinions, we can adapt the consent rules [CITATION_1] to the present setup. For all k \u2208 G, let s k t k \u2208 N. The consent rule with (s t) \u2261 (s k t k ) k\u2208G , denoted by f s t , is defined as follows: for all P \u2208 D, all i \u2208 N, and all k \u2208 G, (i) when P ii = k, k \u2208 f i (P) if and only if |{j \u2208 N : P ji = k}| \u2265 s k ; and (ii) when P ii = k, k / \u2208 f i (P) if and only if |{j \u2208 N : P ji = k}| \u2265 t k .",
  "citation_candidates": [
